Class AdmissionController

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.ComponentI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.ComponentImplementedI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.OfferedI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.RequiredI, AdmissionControllerManagementI, ApplicationRequestI, fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.computers.interfaces.ComputerStateDataConsumerI, fr.upmc.datacenter.interfaces.PushModeControllerI, RingDataI, java.rmi.Remote

    public class AdmissionController
extends fr.upmc.components.AbstractComponent
implements ApplicationRequestI, AdmissionControllerManagementI, fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.computers.interfaces.ComputerStateDataConsumerI, RingDataI, fr.upmc.datacenter.interfaces.PushModeControllerI
    The class AdmissionController implements a component that represents an Admission Controller in a datacenter, receiving new application.

    Description

    The Admission Controller Purpose is to manage the new applications and computers sent to the datacenter. When receiving a computer, he split the cores in multiples Virtual Machines then send it to the Ring Data. The Admission Controller receive new Request Generator through the ApplicationRequestI Interface. When receiving a new request generator, it check if he has enough Virtual Machine at disposition and create a Request Dispatcher linked to the request generator and a Controller linked to the request Dispatcher. He then bind the Virtual Machine to the request Dispatcher. He add the Controller to the Data Ring where Free Virtual Machine that can be used by the controller circulate.
    Author:
    Cédric Ribeiro et Mokrane Kadri
